<br>
The best way to get involved is wait for all three camps to be up, or at least the camp you actually want to 'win' up.  If that camp is in the wrong area, say grimlings have taken bears, but wolves now occupy the S marshes, you'll have to set the 'lings back up to take their camp back.  <br>
<br>
To help with any camp conquest, all you really need to do is set up your group in an area where you can easily reach the defender spawns.  For the S marshes, you want either to the right or left of the chief's hut, for the others, just outside the caves.  As soon as a zonewide message about one group attacking the other goes out, get ready.  Now, at the locations I've mentioned, a group of 'defenders' will pop appropriate to the race being attacked.  A somewhat weaker group of 'invaders' will spawn on the edge of the camp and advance to fight these defenders.  If the defending race is the one you want to win, do nothing, they'll wipe the invaders easily.  If the defending race is one of the two you want out of the picture, pull their defenders.  As soon as the invaders clear the remaining defenders and enter the main part of the camp, it'll respawn as their race.  Once one race controls all three camps, their prince or head guy will spawn in the Vah Shir outpost and wipe the kitties.  He'll be surrounded by a ring of bodyguards, who see invis and are generally annoying.  The prince is the guy who drops all the rare drops in this event.  You get different drops depending on which prince spawns, check Allakhazam's for a list of drops, then click the links or the prince names themselves to see who's got what.  Once the prince is down, the war resets.  I dunno if he leaves a longer corpse now that it's fixed, but before you had to agree with your group on who got what drop ahead of time, so the corpse didn't poof with the zone respawn before you were done arguing over the No-drops.<br>
<br>
Some things to keep in mind:<br>
1. When sonic wolves control any camp but their own, any sonic wolf in the new camp will drop shrieking substances for Shadowscream armor forging.  This can save you a trip to TM, and the drop rate is staggering compared to the TM droprate.<br>
<br>
2. When owlbears control any camp but their own, the bears in the new camps drop wailing substances for Shadowscream armors.  This can save you a major headache in Paludal, as one player will attempt to claim every grimy owlbear in the zone, whether they can reach/clear all three spawnpoints or not.<br>
<br>
3. When grimlings control any camp but their own, grimlings in the new camp will drop Acrylia ore, rarely.  Drop rate isn't fantastic, but if you can figure out where the ore is most likely to drop, you can make out like a bandit.  Hint: ore doesn't drop often from named grimlings, though they do have other nice stuff.<br>
<br>
4. Anytime a new race takes over another's camp, the rare spawns will start spawning as rare members of the new race.  In the case of grimlings, if they take over wolves, Gurn Noeyes will start popping in place of the packleader in the caves.  Noeyes has a very nice caster earring and a charged EB bracer.  <br>
